{"questionId":"22583","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>In this question you will be exploring the strategies required to solve a system of linear differential equations.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Consider the system of linear differential equations of the form:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math>,</p>\n<p>where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;is a parameter.</p>\n<p>First consider the case where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Now consider the case where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>By differentiating&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;with respect to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>, show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mo>d</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mo>d</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mstyle></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22583","referenceCode":"21N.3.AHL.TZ0.2b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By differentiating dydt=-x+y with respect to t, show that d2ydt2=2dydt.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}